                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d710">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/4964: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-25T18:00:00-06:00"
                            >October 25, 1938—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>414. Referring to my telegram No. 400 of October 9, 12 noon. Mr. Sollenberger has
                    informed a member of my staff that appeal entered with administrative
                    authorities (referring to my despatch No. 7495 of October 7, 1938<note n="22"
                        xml:id="d710fn22">Not printed.</note>) has now been denied by these
                    administrative authorities.</p>
                <p>This means that <hi rend="italic">Amparo</hi> action against expropriation decree
                    et cetera will have to be begun all over again in the district courts. It is
                    anticipated that copies of the administrative refusal will be available for
                    transmission by air mail tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Daniels</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
